## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **MySQL Configuration**: You'll need a running MySQL server. The app will use environment variables for DB credentials (`DB_HOST`, `DB_USER`, `DB_PASSWORD`, `DB_NAME`).

> [!NOTE]
> The website content will be in **Gujarati** where appropriate (headings, labels) with English for technical elements. The admin panel will primarily be in English for ease of use.

---

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
1. Start the backend: `cd d:\Learning\Resume\server && npm start`
2. Start the frontend: `cd d:\Learning\Resume\client && npm run dev`
3. Open `http://localhost:5173` in browser
4. Verify: Homepage loads with animations, all pages navigate correctly, responsive at various widths
5. Test admin login at `/admin/login`
6. Verify CRUD operations in admin panel

### Manual Verification
- Check responsive design by resizing browser window
- Verify animations are smooth and not janky
- Test all API endpoints return correct data
- Confirm MySQL tables are created correctly via `schema.sql`
